tful experience </div><div class="t m17b x7d h1c y780 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sacredness desecrated </div><div class="t m55 x7d h1c y681 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Subject of religious </div><div class="t m3e5 x0 h1c y781 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">disputes </div><div class="t m3df x7d h1c y782 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Influenced by </div><div class="t m4ed x0 h1c y783 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pagan practices </div><div class="t m6fb x0 h1c y784 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and philosophies </div><div class="t m508 x29 h1c y785 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath </div><div class="t m2f8 x10 h1d y67d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gen. 2:3 </div><div class="t m27c x29 h1d y77e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ex. 20:8-11 </div><div class="t m6f xc3 h1d y77f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Isa. 58:13, 14 </div><div class="t m29b xc3 h1d y780 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eze. 22:8 </div><div class="t m50 xc3 h1d y786 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 2:23, 24 </div><div class="t m6fc x10 h1d y782 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Observance </div><div class="t m6fd xbf h1d y783 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">changed to </div><div class="t m564 x6c h1d y784 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accommodate </div><div class="t m6fe xbf h1d y787 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">worshipers </div><div class="t m2fc xbb h1c y788 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Marriage </div><div class="t m6ff x79 h1d y789 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Gen. 5:2 </div><div class="t m147 x79 h1d y77e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Isa. 54:5, 6 </div><div class="t m700 x79 h1d y77f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prov. 5:18, 19 </div><div class="t m14d x79 h1d y78a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eze. 22:9-11 </div><div class="t m427 x79 h1d y786 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 10:1-16 </div><div class="t m701 x79 h1d y78b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Conditioned by </div><div class="t m702 xb1 h1d y783 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Greek idea that </div><div class="t m703 xb1 h1d y784 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">body is inferior </div><div class="t m37c xb1 h1d y787 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to soul. </div><div class="t m704 x35 h1c y78c ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God&apos;s ideal distorted. </div><div class="t m705 x66 h1d y78c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Desecration of the Sabbath parallels </div><div class="t m67f x7d h1d y78d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the desecration of marriage. Revival of true Sabbathkeeping </div><div class="t m395 x7d h1d y78e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will be accompanied by revival of Christian marriage. </div><div class="t m706 x35 h1c y78f ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Devaluation of women. </div><div class="t m707 x6d h1d y78f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In pagan cultures, and even among </div><div class="t m708 x7d h1d y790 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the people of God, women were often regarded as property. </div><div class="t m691 x7d h1d y791 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Easy divorce for men, polygamy, and treatment of women as </div><div class="t m4af x7d h1d y792 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">inferiors corrupted God&apos;s plan. </div><div class="t m1c2 x35 h1c y793 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Violations of the marriage covenant: </div><div class="t m709 x75 h1d y793 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">adultery (2 Sam. 11:2, </div><div class="t m27 x7d h1d y794 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4), incest (Eze. 22:9-11), rape (2 Sam. 13:14), bestiality (Lev. </div><div class="t m70a x1c h1d y61 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18:23), homosexuality (Rom. 1:26, 27), prostitution (Judges 16:1), </div><div class="t mbe x7d h1d y1b4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">polygamy (2 Sam. 5:13), divorce, violence, and abuse (Mal. 2:16; </div><div class="t m70b x7d h1d y795 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matt. 19:8). </div><div class="t m70c x35 h1c y796 ff1 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sexual renunciation or permissiveness. </div><div class="t m70d x9d h1d y797 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Throughout the </div><div class="t m70e x7d h1d y798 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Middle Ages celibacy and virginity were thought more holy </div><div class="t m613 x7d h1d y799 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than marriage. This view is still held, though 